The Police in Saselamani near Malamulele are investigating the death of a couple which occurred at Mhinga village. Community members saw flies around the coupleâ€™s house and then alerted the police who acted swiftly. The neighbours last saw the couple three days back and were concerned about their disappearance. The police found the couple dead when they arrived at their house. The man, Gezani Donald Mahori was found hanged inside the house and his wife Fortunate Shopola was found lying dead inside the toilet with multiple wounds to her body. The police said the motive behind the incident and the circumstances thereof is still not clear at this stage but domestic violence may not be ruled out. The Police have encouraged community members to consult their local professionals for intervention whenever they are in any domestic related situation rather that resorting to violence. -TNA Reporter 